  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ContainmentProcess">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which material is enclosed and retained within a defined spatial boundary by a containing artifact.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural boundary maintains separation between internal contents and external environment, preventing uncontrolled release while withstanding internal pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a container artifact encloses and maintains internal components or fluids within its structural boundaries, providing physical separation from the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">containment process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de contenção</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000279">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um interruptor de fluxo é um instrumento que possui uma função de comutação de fluxo para automaticamente abrir ou fechar circuitos elétricos quando a taxa de fluxo de fluido atinge valores de limiar predeterminados.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow switch is an instrument that bears a flow switching function to automatically open or close electrical circuits when fluid flow rate reaches predetermined threshold values.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A functional switch that is intended to give a signal when the flow have reached a pre-set value.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLOW SWITCH&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;PROCESS SWITCH&gt; and a &lt;FLOW MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;, that is specially and exclusively designed for &lt;SWITCHING&gt; at a given &lt;FLOW RATE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1549"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow switch</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">interruptor de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow switch is an instrument that has the function to switch electrical circuits based on flow rate detection at preset thresholds.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowSwitch(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowSwitchingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every valve body is a valve component that contains and supports valve working components and bears the function of fluid and pressure containment.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve body</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3372"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; that is the main fluid or pressure containing component of a valve, housing and supporting the working components</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type - the structural characteristics of being the main pressure-containing housing component are necessary conditions but may not be sufficient under OWA, as various specialized valve body configurations exist that might contain additional components or have hybrid designs that could lead to false positive classifications.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ValveBody(x) → ValveComponent(x) ∧ ∃f(ContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃y(WorkingComponent(y) ∧ houses(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ValveComponent que porta uma ContainmentFunction e que serve como o principal componente de contenção de fluido e pressão de uma válvula, alojando e suportando os componentes de trabalho.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A ValveComponent that bears a ContainmentFunction and that serves as the main fluid and pressure containing component of a valve, housing and supporting the working components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2856">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000195"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000102">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Pump with an impeller or rotor that spins in a housing and the drag forces on the fluids cause them to flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A dynamic pump utilizing impellers provided with vanes generating centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A dynamic pump that contains impellers provided with vanes to generate centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL PUMP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PUMP&gt; in which centrifugal force imparted by impeller is convered to pressure in the volute casing. NOTE - Combine with either  BARE PUMP or PUMP SYSTEM,</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of pump commonly used in the handling and mixing of oilfield fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000102"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CentrifugalPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃y(CentrifugalImpeller(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(VoluteCasing(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba centrífuga</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb436"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb435"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal pump is a pump that has a centrifugal impeller as component part at all times and has a volute casing as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifugal pump is a pump that uses centrifugal force generated by rotating impellers with vanes to increase fluid pressure through a volute casing.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba centrífuga é uma bomba que usa força centrífuga gerada por impulsores rotativos com pás para aumentar a pressão do fluido através de uma carcaça voluta.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any equipment with centrifugal impellers and volute casing could be inferred as a standard centrifugal pump, potentially misclassifying specialized hybrid equipment or complex pump systems that contain centrifugal stages but serve different operational roles.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000110">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1024"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de pressão diferencial é um transmissor de pressão que possui uma função de transmissão de pressão diferencial, permitindo medir a diferença de pressão entre dois sinais de pressão de entrada e transmitir essa diferença como um sinal de saída padronizado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that bears a differential pressure transmission function, enabling it to measure the pressure difference between two input pressure signals and transmit this difference as a standardized output signal.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received pressure difference signal.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DifferentialPressureTransmitter(x) ↔ PressureTransmitter(x) ∧ ∃f (DifferentialPressureTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that bears a differential pressure transmission function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ThreePhaseSeparationFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3181"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000195"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3180"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de separação trifásica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">three phase separation function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000123">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every globe valve is a valve that has as component part at all times a linear motion closure and a normal seat.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1771"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1770"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GLOBE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve whose closure element is a flat disc or conical plug sealing on a seat that is usually parallel to the flow axis.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula globo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">globe valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A globe valve is a valve characterized by a closure member (disc or plug) that operates with linear motion perpendicular to a seat that is oriented normal to the fluid flow path.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula globo é uma válvula caracterizada por um elemento de fechamento (disco ou tampão) que opera com movimento linear perpendicular a uma sede orientada normal ao caminho do fluxo do fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GlobeValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y,z(hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y) ∧ LinearMotionClosure(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z) ∧ NormalSeat(z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under OWA, making the structural differentia sufficient could force classification of specialized equipment containing linear motion closures (like complex multi-way valves or custom manifolds) as standard globe valves when they may warrant distinct maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000236">
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000236"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">torre de resfriamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cooling tower</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A cooler and an air cooled heat exchanger that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler and an air cooled heat exchanger that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COOLING TOWER&gt; is an &lt;AIR COOLED HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; and a &lt;TOWER&gt; that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CoolingTower(x) ↔ HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃t(Tower(t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t)) ∧ ∃p(ConvectiveAirCirculationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cooling tower is a heat exchanger that incorporates a tall tower structure through which air circulates by convection to remove heat from process fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma torre de resfriamento é um trocador de calor que incorpora uma estrutura de torre alta através da qual o ar circula por convecção para remover calor de fluidos de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb715"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cooling tower is a heat exchanger that has a tower structure as component part at all times and participates in convective air circulation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2404">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PipeInterior"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb19">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AccumulationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle é uma válvula que é equipada com um atuador e regula a vazão de fluido em resposta a sinais de controle de um sistema de controle de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A control valve is a valve that is equipped with an actuator and regulates fluid flow rate in response to control signals from a process control system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb663"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb664"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to modify (regulate)  the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; is a &lt;VALVE&gt; and an &lt;FINAL CONTROL FUNCTION&gt;, operated by an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; that can be used to modify the fluid flow rate in response to a signal from a &lt;CONTROLLER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Modulating valve that controls either the flow rate, liquid level, or pressure in process equipment. In the latter case, it is often referred to as a (pressure) regulator.                   (Note - Typically, high pressure gas from the pipeline is used as the supply medium needed to energize the valve actuator.) https://www.ipieca.org/resources/methane-emissions-glossary</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to modify (regulate) the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device, other than a common, hand-actuated process block valve or self-actuated check valve, that directly manipulates the flow of one or more fluid process streams.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve that controls a process variable, such as pressure, flow or temperature, by modulating its opening in response to a signal from a controller.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Control valve is a functional type where identity is grounded in the designed function to regulate flow in response to control signals. This functional identity cannot be reduced to structural checklists as the same function can be realized through many different physical mechanisms (ball, butterfly, globe, gate, etc.). The presence of actuator and flow control element are necessary but not sufficient - the key is the integration for automated flow modulation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">control valve</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every control valve is a valve that has an actuator as component part and has a flow control function and participates in flow control processes by receiving control signals and modulating fluid flow.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ControlValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃a(Actuator(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,a)) ∧ ∃f(FlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∀p(participatesIn(x,p) ∧ FlowControlProcess(p) → ∃s(ControlSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(p,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb476">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000161"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de retenção é uma válvula que possui uma função de prevenção de refluxo, permitindo automaticamente que o fluido flua em apenas uma direção enquanto previne o fluxo reverso.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A check valve is a valve that bears a backflow prevention function, automatically permitting fluid to flow in one direction only while preventing reverse flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A valve that only allows flow in one direction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A mechanical device that permits fluid to flow or pressure to act in one direction only.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that permits fluid to flow in one direction only.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that permits fluid to flow in one direction only.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE&gt; is a &lt;VALVE&gt; that permits fluid to flow in one direction only</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValve(x) ↔ Valve(x) ∧ ∃f(BackflowPreventionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb459"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de retenção</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every check valve is a valve that has the function to prevent backflow and automatically allow unidirectional fluid flow.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LiquidOutlet">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">liquid outlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">saída líquido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Outlet"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2472">
