  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000315">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MOTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DRIVER(function)&gt; that is powered by electricity or internal combustion</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A driver that is powered by electricity or internal combustion (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A device that generates rotational kinetic energy.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">motor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every motor is an assembly that has the function of generating mechanical energy and has as output rotational kinetic energy.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A motor is an assembly that bears a mechanical energy generation function to convert electrical, chemical, pneumatic, or hydraulic energy into rotational mechanical energy.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor é um conjunto que possui uma função de geração de energia mecânica para converter energia elétrica, química, pneumática ou hidráulica em energia mecânica rotacional.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2261"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Motor(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(MechanicalEnergyGenerationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(RotationalKineticEnergy(e) ∧ hasOutput(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2419">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BentPipeSection"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2295">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BinaryFlowControlProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000208">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb61"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An agitator is a mixer that stirs or shakes fluids by reaction force from moving vanes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um agitador é um misturador que mexe ou agita fluidos por força de reação de palhetas móveis.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Agitator(x) ↔ Mixer(x) ∧ ∃f(AgitationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃v(MovingVane(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every agitator is a mixer that has the function to agitate fluids and has moving vanes as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An Agitator is a dynamic mixer that stirs or shakes fluids by reaction force from moving vanes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;AGITATOR&gt; is a &lt;DYNAMIC MIXER&gt; that stirs or shakes fluids by reaction force from moving vanes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A propeller like device with agitational or rotational movement located in a tank to prevent the content of the tank to build component segments.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">agitator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">agitador</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000214">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A large area with a general containment and an often thick accumulation of rock. A sedimentary basin is an area of regional settling that can be characterized in space, time, and sedimentary fill .It is a physical depression at the earth's surface which accumulates and preserves sediments. The scale of basins varies greatly, from ocean basins to small ponds.                  ==References==                   Helwig, J. A. 1985. Origin and Classification of Sedimentary Basins. Offshore Technology Conference. http://www.doi.org/doi:10.4043/4843-MS</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A container intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BASIN&gt; is a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;, intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A depression in the crust of the Earth, caused by plate tectonic activity and subsidence, in which sediments accumulate.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A basin is a vessel that is designed to store liquid or solid material, characterized by being typically open at the top and installed partly or totally below grade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bacia é um vaso projetado para armazenar material líquido ou sólido, caracterizado por ser tipicamente aberto no topo e instalado parcial ou totalmente abaixo do nível do solo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">Basin(x) ↔ Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(StorageFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(OpenTop(p) ∧ hasGeometricProperty(x,p)) ∧ ∃q(PartlyBelowGrade(q) ∧ hasInstallationProperty(x,q))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000214"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bacia</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">basin</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb187"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every basin is a vessel that bears a storage function and has an open top configuration and is installed partly below grade.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb405">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CasingWall"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000276">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlashDrum(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(FlashVaporizationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1458"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flash drum is a separator that performs flash vaporization to separate lighter components (which vaporize and are drawn off at the top) from heavier components (which remain liquid and are drawn off at the bottom).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tambor de flash é um separador que realiza vaporização flash para separar componentes mais leves (que vaporizam e são retirados no topo) de componentes mais pesados (que permanecem líquidos e são retirados no fundo).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flash drum</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tambor de flash</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flash drum is a separator that bears a flash vaporization function and has a vapor outlet, liquid outlet, and feed inlet.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tank or vessel in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainder heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLASH DRUM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VESSEL&gt; in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainer heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb191">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000158"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb192"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000273">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1389"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1390"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1391"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLANGE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar, or rib for strength or for attachment to another object</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar or rib.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A common, high pressure wellhead connection, using bolt attached flange plates and metal-to-metal seals.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A connection profile used in pipe work and associated equipment to provide a means of assembling and disassembling components.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flange is a material artifact characterized by a projecting flat rim, plate, collar, or rib geometry, designed to provide mechanical connection between components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um flange é um artefato material caracterizado por uma geometria de aro plano projetante, placa, colar ou nervura, projetado para fornecer conexão mecânica entre componentes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by structural geometry. Under OWA, any artifact with projecting flat rim geometry would be forced into the flange category, which could incorrectly classify specialized equipment or complex assemblies that contain flange-like features but serve different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flange is a material artifact that has a projecting flat rim geometry and has the function of mechanically connecting components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flange</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">flange</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Flange(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃g(ProjectingFlatRimGeometry(g) ∧ hasCharacteristic(x,g)) ∧ ∃f(MechanicalConnectionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb626">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CondensationFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ConnectionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1385"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb743"/>
