    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DegassingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidDistributionFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fluid distribution function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de distribuição de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2200"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1797"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1798"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2199"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000113">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ELECTRIC MOTOR&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC ROTATING MACHINE&gt; and a &lt;MOTOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRIC TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An electric machine for transforming electric energy into mechanical energy.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An electric machine for transforming electric energy into mechanical energy</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electric motor</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every electric motor is an assembly that bears an electric-to-mechanical conversion function and has component parts including a stator and rotor at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1186"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ElectricMotor(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricToMechanicalConversionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(Stator(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃r(Rotor(r) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor elétrico é um conjunto que possui uma função de conversão de energia elétrica para mecânica e tem tanto um estator quanto um rotor como componentes essenciais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An electric motor is an assembly that bears an electric-to-mechanical energy conversion function and has both a stator and rotor as essential components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000269">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While finned tubes are the defining structural feature, making sufficient conditions (equivalence) under Open World Assumption could lead to false positives where any assembly containing finned tubes would be classified as this specific heat exchanger type, including complex multi-function equipment or specialized hybrid systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1335"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1333"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1332"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1334"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor de tubos aletados é um trocador de calor que possui tubos aletados como mecanismo primário de aumento da superfície de transferência de calor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as the primary heat transfer surface enhancement mechanism.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A heat exchange that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A heat exchanger that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FINNED TUBE HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is an &lt;INDIRECT CONTACT HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; that has finned tubes</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FinnedTubeHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(FinnedTube(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor de tubos aletados</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">finned tube heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2294">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BinaryFlowControlProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000231">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Invólucro que é destinado a abrigar componentes internos do compressor, incluindo o eixo com impulsores e outros componentes mecânicos específicos do compressor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Casing that is intended for housing compressor internals including the shaft with impellers and other compressor-specific mechanical components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for compressor-specific casing identity could lead to false positives where any enclosure intended for compressors might be classified as a standard compressor casing, including specialized or hybrid enclosures that warrant distinct classification.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CompressorCasing(x) → (Casing(x) ∧ ∃y (Compressor(y) ∧ intendedForUseWith(x,y))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">CompressorCasing ⊑ Casing ⊓ ∃intendedForUseWith.Compressor</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COMPRESSOR CASING&gt; is a  &lt;CASING&gt; that is the typical enclosure for compressors housing the shaft with impeller(s) and other compressor internals</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb618"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">Invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compressor casing</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000197">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3049"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3048"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb184"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000025"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb183"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de armazenamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">storage function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000256">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In the context of acidizing, a diverter is a material that forces acid to enter another zone by having a higher viscosity or building a filter cake.                  In the context of a wellhead, a diverter is a device in the flowpath at the wellhead that forces fluid to go down a pipe to a pit or tank.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIVERTER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;DIVERTING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A chemical agent or mechanical device used in injection treatments, such as matrix stimulation, to ensure a uniform distribution of treatment fluid across the treatment interval.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A 'device' that is providing diversion of something from an expected course or direction.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um diverter é um artefato material que possui uma função projetada para desviar ou redirecionar materiais, fluidos ou fluxos de seu curso esperado para caminhos ou destinos alternativos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diverter is a material artifact that bears a designed function to divert or redirect materials, fluids, or flows from their expected course to alternative paths or destinations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diverter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">diverter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diverter is a material artifact that has the function of diverting materials or flows from expected paths to alternative destinations.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1079"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Diverter(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(DivertingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000253">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Diffuser(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnergyDiffusionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um difusor é um conjunto que tem a função projetada de converter energia cinética do fluxo de fluido em energia de pressão através de desaceleração controlada em uma passagem divergente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diffuser is an assembly that has the designed function of converting kinetic energy of fluid flow into pressure energy through controlled deceleration in a diverging passage.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that contains a diverging channel-shaped chamber in which part of the kinetic energy of the fluid is converted into pressure energy.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFUSER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;DIFFUSING&gt; which is used in pumps to convert kinetic energy imparted by impeller to potential energy i.e. pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">difusor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diffuser</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diffuser is an assembly that bears an energy diffusion function and has a diverging channel as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1032"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3221">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MagneticCore"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000216">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A bell nipple is a pipe that conducts drilling fluids in drilling operations and is characterized by an enlarged diameter that serves as a funnel and a location at the wellhead assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um bell nipple é um tubo que conduz fluidos de perfuração em operações de perfuração e é caracterizado por um diâmetro alargado que serve como funil e uma localização no conjunto da cabeça do poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(BellNipple(x) ↔ (Pipe(x) ∧ ∃f(DrillingFluidConductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(EnlargedDiameter(s) ∧ hasCharacteristicShape(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(WellheadAssembly(l) ∧ hasLocation(x,l))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A Bell nipple is a section of large diameter pipe fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BELL NIPPLE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a large diameter &lt;PIPING NETWORK SEGMENT&gt; fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A funnel shaped pipe at the top of the casing that guides tool string entry and may have a side port for fluid pumping.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bell nipple</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bell nipple</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb235"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every bell nipple is a pipe that bears a DrillingFluidConductionFunction and has an enlarged diameter shape and is located at a wellhead assembly.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000216"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb469">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
