    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ReactiveHeatingFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CombustionChamber">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">câmara de combustão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">combustion chamber</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000287">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any of several replaceable seals in equipment or tools.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GASKET&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SEAL&gt; that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1682"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">junta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gasket</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Gasket(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SealingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(DeformableMaterial(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃g(ClosedLoopGeometry(g) ∧ hasProperty(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gasket is a material artifact that has component part some deformable material and bears some sealing function and has property some closed loop geometry.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gasket is a material artifact made of deformable material arranged in closed loops that bears a sealing function to prevent leakage between mating surfaces with limited relative movement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma junta é um artefato material feito de material deformável arranjado em loops fechados que possui uma função de vedação para prevenir vazamentos entre superfícies de acoplamento com movimento relativo limitado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000109">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gauge that is intended for measuring and indicating pressure differences.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DifferentialPressureGauge(x) ↔ PressureGauge(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)) ∧ ∃p(PressurePortPair(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um manômetro de pressão diferencial é um manômetro que mede e indica a diferença entre duas entradas de pressão usando um elemento de medição de pressão diferencial.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure gauge is a pressure gauge that measures and indicates the difference between two pressure inputs using a differential pressure measuring element.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure gauge is a pressure gauge that bears a DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction and has component parts including a DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement and PressurePortPair.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure gauge</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">manômetro de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb985"/>
  </rdf:Description>
