  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000374">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma parte de objeto por fiat que é o limite estrutural externo de contenção de pressão de um vaso, projetada para encerrar e isolar o conteúdo interno enquanto suporta cargas de pressão interna.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fiat object part that is the outer pressure-containing structural boundary of a vessel, designed to enclose and isolate internal contents while withstanding internal pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL SHELL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SHELL(structure)&gt; that is all or part of the pressure containing outer part of a vessel</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">VesselShell SubClassOf: FiatObjectPart and partOf some Vessel and bearerOf some PressureContainmentFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural configuration as outer pressure-containing part of vessel. Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions are difficult to establish - other structural components might also be pressure-containing parts of vessels in specialized designs.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3418"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VesselShell(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Vessel(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PressureContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel shell</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">parte de objeto por fiat</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000317">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo de saída</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">output shaft</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Shaft that participates in mechanical energy output processes, serving as the exit point for mechanical energy transmission from a prime mover to external energy consuming equipment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Eixo que participa em processos de saída de energia mecânica, servindo como ponto de saída para transmissão de energia mecânica de um motor primário para equipamentos consumidores de energia externos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2322"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (OutputShaft(x) → Shaft(x) ∧ ∃p (MechanicalEnergyOutputProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃f (PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on positional role within mechanical systems. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would be difficult to specify without risk of misclassifying intermediate shafts or complex multi-shaft arrangements that happen to have output characteristics.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;OUTPUT SHAFT&gt; is a &lt;SHAFT&gt; that is the exit of mechanical energy and driver of an external energy consumer.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every output shaft is a shaft that participates in at least one mechanical energy output process and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SubsurfaceResourceInteractionProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de interação com recursos subsuperficiais</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">subsurface resource interaction process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000369">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vacuum column</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de vácuo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A vacuum column is a distillation column that is designed to withstand outside pressure during vacuum operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma coluna de vácuo é uma coluna de destilação projetada para resistir à pressão externa durante operação sob vácuo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vacuum column is a distillation column that bears a vacuum pressure resistance quality.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000255"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3351"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3349"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3350"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VACUUM COLUMN&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DISTILLATION COLUMN&gt; intended to withstand outside pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VacuumColumn(x) → DistillationColumn(x) ∧ ∃q(VacuumPressureResistanceQuality(q) ∧ bearerOf(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural capability. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for vacuum-capable design would be complex and could lead to false positives. The structural differentia (vacuum resistance) requires domain expert validation of what constitutes adequate vacuum design capability.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000138">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PISTON CHECK VALVE&gt; is a &lt;LIFT CHECK VALVE&gt; and a &lt;PISTON VALVE&gt; that has a free gravity or spring loaded piston type closure member</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A lift check valve that has a free gravity or spring loaded piston type closure member.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A lift check valve that has a free gravity or spring loaded piston type closure member.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every piston check valve is a check valve that has a piston closure as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A piston check valve is a check valve that has a piston-type closure member that moves linearly along the flow axis under gravity or spring loading to prevent backflow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de retenção tipo pistão é uma válvula de retenção que possui um elemento de fechamento tipo pistão que se move linearmente ao longo do eixo de fluxo sob ação da gravidade ou mola para prevenir refluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2472"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PistonCheckValve(x) → CheckValve(x) ∧ ∃y(PistonClosure(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de retenção tipo pistão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">piston check valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any artifact with a piston closure could potentially be classified as piston check valve, but specialized hybrid valves or custom manifolds containing piston mechanisms should not be automatically asserted into this standard maintenance category without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1385">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ConnectionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
