  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowModificationProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which the characteristics of fluid flow are altered by a flow modification accessory, resulting in changes to flow patterns, velocity profiles, turbulence levels, or pressure drop characteristics while the fluid passes through or around the device.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow modification process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de modificação de fluxo</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb321">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb322"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaft is an assembly that transmits power through rotation and has shaft keys, shaft seals, and shaft sleeves as essential components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2912"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2913"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2914"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2911"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for shaft identity could lead to false positives - any assembly with a shaft key and rotational motion might be classified as a shaft rather than a more specific equipment type that contains a shaft. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to validate sufficiency.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has component parts including shaft keys for torque transmission and shaft seals for leakage prevention, serving as the core rotating element in rotating machinery.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui partes componentes incluindo chavetas de eixo para transmissão de torque e vedações de eixo para prevenção de vazamento, servindo como o elemento rotativo central em máquinas rotativas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ENGINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the core rotating element on which the rotating parts are mounted and through which energy is either transmitted from the prime mover or generated in case of a driver.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Shaft(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃k(ShaftKey(k) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,k)) ∧ ∃s(ShaftSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(ShaftSleeve(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000340">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2773"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTARY ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; causing a rotary motion</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on rotary motion mechanism. Under OWA, providing sufficient conditions could lead to over-classification where any equipment that happens to produce rotary motion (motors, turbines, etc.) might be incorrectly classified as rotary actuators. The rotary motion differentia is necessary but requires domain expert validation to confirm it is sufficient for the actuator equipment category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador rotativo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotary actuator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every rotary actuator is an actuator that participates in rotary motion processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A rotary actuator is an actuator that causes rotary motion by converting control signals into controlled rotational mechanical output.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador rotativo é um atuador que causa movimento rotativo convertendo sinais de controle em saída mecânica rotacional controlada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (RotaryActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃p (RotaryMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3282">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3283"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3277"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000345">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Scrubber(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f,p,g,l (SeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f) ∧ LiquidWashingProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p) ∧ GasPortion(g) ∧ LiquidPortion(l) ∧ hasInput(x,g) ∧ hasInput(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A reactor that removes various components from produced gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SCRUBBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device to remove dirt, water, foreign matter, or undesired liquids that are part of the gas flowstream.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2855"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um lavador de gases é um separador que limpa gás através da lavagem do fluxo gasoso com líquido para remover contaminantes como poeira, partículas ou substâncias indesejadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A scrubber is a separator that cleans gas by washing the gas flow with liquid to remove contaminants such as dust, particles, or undesired substances.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every scrubber is a separator that has the function of separation and participates in liquid washing processes with both gas and liquid inputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scrubber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">lavador de gases</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidDirectionProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fluid direction process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de direcionamento de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1105">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PowerTransmissionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000106">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb558"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb550"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CIRCUIT BREAKER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL APPARATUS&gt; and a &lt;SWITCHING DEVICE&gt; that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disjuntor é um dispositivo de chaveamento elétrico que possui uma função de interrupção de corrente elétrica e participa regularmente em processos que interrompem com segurança a corrente elétrica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disjuntor é um equipamento elétrico que possui uma função de proteção de circuito e participa em processos de interrupção de corrente em intervalos regulares.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A circuit breaker is a material artifact that bears an electrical current interruption function and regularly participates in processes that safely interrupt electrical current.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A circuit-breaker is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and participates in current interruption processes at regular intervals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every circuit breaker is an electrical switching device that has the function to interrupt electrical current and participates in regular current interruption processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every circuit-breaker is an electrical equipment that has the function to protect circuits and participates in the process of interrupting electrical current at regular intervals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">disjuntor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">circuit breaker</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CircuitBreaker(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(CurrentInterruptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CircuitBreaker(x) ↔ ElectricalSwitchingDevice(x) ∧ ∃f (ElectricalCurrentInterruptionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p (RegularInterruptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000106"/>
  </rdf:Description>
