  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000305">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INJECTION WELL&gt; is  a &lt;WELL&gt; with the purpose of injecting a material into a reservoir, normally with a pressure higher than the formation pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A well in which fluids are injected rather than produced, the primary objective typically being to maintain reservoir pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A well either specifically drilled, or, more likely, a poor producer that is converted to inject fluids to stabilize the decline of pressure in a productive zone. An injector is required to have a pressure connection to the pay and to a producing well. Water is typically injected at the base of the pay or, in a gas well, or gas is injected into the gas cap.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection well</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2018"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (InjectionWell(x) ↔ (Well(x) ∧ ∃f (InjectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every injection well is a well that has the function to inject materials into a reservoir under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço de injeção é um poço que possui a função projetada de injetar materiais em um reservatório a uma pressão superior à pressão da formação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An injection well is a well that bears the designed function of injecting materials into a reservoir at pressure higher than formation pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1140">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DischargeOutlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000289">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While the gear mechanism is definitionally necessary for gear pumps, making it sufficient under OWA could lead to false positives - any complex equipment containing gears (like gearboxes with integrated pumps or multi-function units) might be incorrectly classified as standard gear pumps for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de engrenagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GearPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃g,c (GearMechanism(g) ∧ PumpCasing(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1725"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1726"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1729"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1727"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1728"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR PUMP&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY PUMP&gt; that contains gear teeth within an casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary pump that contains gear teeth within an casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures and by which gear meshing serves as reverse flow seal.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gear pump is a pump that contains gear teeth within a casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures through meshing action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de engrenagem é uma bomba que contém dentes de engrenagem dentro de um invólucro ou carcaça para transportar líquido em pressões de retorno relativamente altas através de ação de engrenamento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gear pump is a pump that has as component part at all times a gear mechanism and a pump casing, and bears a pumping function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HeatTransferBundle">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">feixe de calor de transferência</rdfs:label>
