  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConnectionProcess">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which two or more electrical conductor parts are held in intimate contact by an electrical connector, resulting in a conductive path that enables electrical current flow through the connection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical connection process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de conexão elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2217">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MaterialProcessingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SetPointAdjustmentMechanism">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">set point adjustment mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo de ajuste de ponto de ajuste</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000364">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TUBING HANGER&gt; is a &lt;WELL STRING HANGER&gt; that is installed on top of the tubing string and supports the string when landed in the tubing hanger or tubing head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device attached to the topmost tubing joint in the wellhead to support the tubing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A slip set or donut that suspends and holds the top of the tubing in the wellhead.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well string hanger that is used for production tubing. The tubing hanger incorporates a sealing system to ensure that the tubing conduit and annulus are hydraulically isolated.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TubingHanger(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(TubingSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SealingSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃m(SupportMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃c(TubingConnection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing hanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">suporte de coluna de produção</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um suporte de coluna de produção é um conjunto que suporta colunas de produção em cabeças de poço com vedação integrada para isolar o conduto da coluna do anular.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A tubing hanger is an assembly that supports tubing strings in wellheads with integrated sealing to isolate tubing conduit from annulus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3253"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every tubing hanger is an assembly that bears a tubing support function and has component parts including a sealing system, support mechanism, and tubing connection.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2009">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000178">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de medição de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure measurement function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2611"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2610"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000028"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000333">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A FiatObjectPart that is the secondary winding of a power transformer and that bears a SecondaryWindingFunction consisting in delivering transformed electrical power at the output voltage level.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma FiatObjectPart que é o enrolamento secundário de um transformador de potência e que possui uma SecondaryWindingFunction consistindo em fornecer energia elétrica transformada no nível de tensão de saída.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">enrolamento secundário de transformador de potência</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">power transformer secondary winding</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">PowerTransformerSecondaryWinding SubClassOf FiatObjectPart and (partOf some PowerTransformer) and (hasFunction some SecondaryWindingFunction)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SecondaryWinding"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2592"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POWER TRANSFORMER SECONDARY WINDING&gt; is a &lt;TRANSFORMER SECONDARY WINDING&gt; intended to be the secondary winding of a power transformer</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PowerTransformerSecondaryWinding(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(PowerTransformer(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(SecondaryWindingFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification basis - the physical configuration (being the secondary winding of a power transformer) provides necessary conditions, but sufficient conditions are harder to assert under OWA without risking false positives for specialized or hybrid transformer configurations.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000124">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1832"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Heater(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(HeatingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heater</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aquecedor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aquecedor é um conjunto que possui uma função de aquecimento para adicionar energia térmica a um meio.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A heater is an assembly that bears a heating function to add thermal energy to a medium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every heater is an assembly that bears a heating function and has heating elements and housing as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HEATER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;HEATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An apparatus or machine that has the capability of heating.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Equipment that transfers heat to the produced gas stream.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000189">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transmissão de vibração</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vibration transmission function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3420"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3419"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000068">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1810"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1809"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2476"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb74"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1821"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2477"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2950"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2949"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1328"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1820"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb75"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1329"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a HeatTransferProcess and that consists in facilitating the transfer of thermal energy between two or more fluid media while maintaining their physical separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transferência de calor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat transfer function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000320">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A facility on a pipeline for inserting and retrieving a scraper or pig.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] "</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIG TRAP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TOOL&gt; that is a pipeline maintenance tool, which includes a launcher and receiver, introducing a &lt;PIPE PIG&gt; into the line</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PigTrap(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PigLaunchingAndReceivingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃l(PigLauncher(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)) ∧ ∃r(PigReceiver(r) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pig trap is an assembly that bears a pig launching and receiving function and has component parts that are a pig launcher and a pig receiver.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2379"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">armadilha de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig trap</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma armadilha de pig é um conjunto que possui a função de lançar e receber pigs de tubulação para manutenção de dutos e possui componentes de lançador e receptor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pig trap is an assembly that bears the function of launching and receiving pipe pigs for pipeline maintenance and has both launcher and receiver components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
