  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StationaryMachineComponentFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3045"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3044"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de componente estacionário de máquina</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stationary machine component function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a StationaryMachineComponentProcess and that consists in providing a stationary structural foundation and housing for active elements (such as windings, vanes, or seals) within rotating machinery, maintaining positional stability relative to moving components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000225">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb446"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb445"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb447"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb448"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'separator' and 'machine' that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGE&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE&gt; and a &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device that separates materials by density through a centrifugal motion.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An item of solids-removal equipment that removes fine and ultrafine solids.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Centrifuge(x) → Separator(x) ∧ ∃d (RotatingDrum(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃p (CentrifugalForceProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma centrífuga é um separador que usa força centrífuga gerada por um tambor rotativo para separar fases de diferentes densidades.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifuge is a separator that uses centrifugal force generated by a rotating drum to separate phases of different densities.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Although functionally defined as a separator, the constructive differentia (centrifugal mechanism) makes sufficient conditions complex under OWA. Any equipment with a rotating drum could potentially be classified as a centrifuge even if designed for other purposes (mixing, drying, etc.). Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifuge</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">centrífuga</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifuge is a separator that has a rotating drum as component part and participates in centrifugal force processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000098">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">blower</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">soprador</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000098"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object intended to compress and supply air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BLOWER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;BLOWING&gt; a medium volume flow</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to compress and supply air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Blower(x) ↔ (Compressor(x) ∧ ∃f,p,v (CompressionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f) ∧ MediumPressureRange(p) ∧ MediumVolumeFlowRange(v) ∧ hasOperatingParameter(x,p) ∧ hasOperatingParameter(x,v))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every blower is a compressor that has the function of compressing gas and operates at medium pressure and medium volume flow ranges.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb273"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A blower is a compressor that compresses and supplies air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um soprador é um compressor que comprime e fornece ar ou gás em pressão média e vazão volumétrica média.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000086">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transformer is an electrical equipment that bears an electrical power transformation function and has component parts including primary winding, secondary winding, and magnetic core.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transformer that, by electromagnetic induction, transforms a system of alternating voltage and current into another system of voltage and current usually of different values and at the same frequency for the purpose of transmitting electrical power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSFORMER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC TO ELECTRIC ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is capable of &lt;TRANSFORMING&gt; power from one circuit to another without changing frequency and works on the principle of mutual induction</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that transforms continuous currents from one voltage to another, or continuous into alternating currents or vice versa.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transformer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transformador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transformer is an electrical equipment that transforms electrical power from one circuit to another at the same frequency through electromagnetic induction using windings and a magnetic core.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transformador é um equipamento elétrico que transforma energia elétrica de um circuito para outro na mesma frequência através de indução eletromagnética usando enrolamentos e um núcleo magnético.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Transformer(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalPowerTransformationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(PrimaryWinding(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(SecondaryWinding(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃c(MagneticCore(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3217"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2849">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SeparationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000241">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb790"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">degasser</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">degaseificador</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device that removes air or gases (methane, H2S, CO2, and others) from drilling liquids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A device that removes air or gases (methane, H2S, CO2 and others) from drilling liquids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any device that helps remove gas from circulated fluid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DEGASSER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a  &lt;FLASH SEPARATOR&gt; that is a device used in drilling to remove gasses from drilling fluid which could otherwise form bubbles</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um degaseificador é um separador que remove gases de fluidos de perfuração realizando uma função de degaseificação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A degasser is a separator that removes gases from drilling fluids by realizing a degassing function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Degasser(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f (DegassingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every degasser is a separator that bears a degassing function and has drilling fluid as input and degassed drilling fluid plus separated gases as outputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb384">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
