  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1267">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1268"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1264"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HydraulicFluidInlet">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic fluid inlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">entrada hidráulico de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPort"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2789"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Rotor(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃p(RotationalMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(RotorShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that participates in rotational motion and has a rotor shaft as an essential component, designed to transfer mechanical energy through rotational motion within a machine assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que participa em movimento rotacional e tem um eixo do rotor como componente essencial, projetado para transferir energia mecânica através de movimento rotacional dentro de um conjunto de máquina.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Rotor is an Assembly that participates in some RotationalMotionProcess and has some rotor shaft as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating shaft in a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the rotating portion of a machine</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration (rotating portion with shaft), providing sufficient conditions under OWA could lead to overclassification. Complex assemblies containing rotating elements might be incorrectly classified as rotors rather than their proper categories (motors, compressors, etc.).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000101">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000073"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb424"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb425"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal compressor is a compressor that has component part at all times some centrifugal impeller and participates in some radial flow pattern.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um compressor centrífugo é um compressor que usa um ou mais impelidores centrífugos para acelerar o gás através de fluxo radial e gerar aumento de pressão por ação centrífuga.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifugal compressor is a compressor that uses one or more centrifugal impellers to accelerate gas through radial flow and generate pressure increase by centrifugal action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type because under OWA, any equipment with a centrifugal impeller could be incorrectly classified as a standard centrifugal compressor, including specialized hybrid equipment or multi-stage systems that contain centrifugal elements but should not be forced into this maintenance category. Domain expert validation needed to confirm structural differentia is sufficient.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CentrifugalCompressor(x) → Compressor(x) ∧ ∃i(CentrifugalImpeller(i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i)) ∧ ∃p(RadialFlowPattern(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL COMPRESSOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;COMPRESSOR&gt; in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial, and generates pressure increase by means of centrifugal action and a volute or diffuser casing.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal compressor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">compressor centrífugo</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000101"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000116">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow element is an instrument that bears a FlowMeasurementFunction and has component parts including a FlowSensingElement and SignalGenerationComponent.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de vazão</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowElement(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de vazão é um instrumento que tem a função de medir vazões em um fluxo e produzir sinais proporcionais à vazão medida.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow element is an instrument that has the function to measure flow rates in a flowstream and produce signals proportional to the measured flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1489"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detecting element that is producing a signal that is proportional to a flow rate.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A device located in a flowstream measuring the flow.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1645">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1642"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000325">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2448"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2446"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2445"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2447"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe tee is a pipe that has exactly three fluid ports arranged in T-configuration and bears a fluid conduction function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. The T-shaped geometric configuration with three specific ports is a structural differentia that is harder to make sufficient under OWA. Custom manifolds or complex fittings might contain T-shaped passages but should not be automatically classified as standard pipe tees without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PipeTee(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃p1,p2,p3(BranchPort(p1) ∧ RunPort(p2) ∧ RunPort(p3) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p1) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p2) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p3) ∧ perpendicularTo(p1,p2) ∧ perpendicularTo(p1,p3)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tê de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe tee</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tê de tubulação é uma conexão de tubulação que possui três portas de fluido dispostas em configuração em formato de T, com uma porta de ramal perpendicular a duas portas de passagem, projetada para realizar função de condução de fluido através de divisão ou combinação de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe tee is a pipe fitting that has three fluid ports arranged in T-shaped configuration, with one branch port perpendicular to two run ports, designed to realize fluid conduction function through flow division or combination.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE TEE&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;PIPING NETWORK NODE&gt; and three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000082">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MeasuringElement que possui uma FlowMeasurementFunction e que é projetado para determinar e quantificar a taxa de fluxo de fluido através de um sistema.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MeasuringElement that bears a FlowMeasurementFunction and that is designed to determine and quantify the rate of fluid flow through a system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MeasuringElement que possui uma FlowMeasurementFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow measuring element</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowMeasuringElement(x) ↔ (MeasuringElement(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLOW MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; is  a &lt;MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; that is used to measure &lt;FLOW RATE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1510"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every FlowMeasuringElement is a MeasuringElement that bears a FlowMeasurementFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1212">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConnectionFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PhysicalVariable">
