  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000303">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A furnace that is intended for the combustion of waste material.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INCINERATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FURNACE&gt; that is intended for the combustion of waste material</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Also known as an enclosed combustor                  Flares are not 100% efficient, and some methane (un-combusted) is emitted during flaring as a result of un-combusted gas being released via the equipment exhaust stream. Flares cannot be performance tested to guarantee that they achieve the same efficiency as an incinerator or enclosed combustor. Studies suggest that the efficiency of a flare during windy conditions can be as low as 50%. The many components and complex network of small gathering lines in flare are a source of fugitive emissions.                  Incinerators are used when flaring is not a viable option. The combustion efficiency of an incinerator is known to be over 99% which is higher than a flare. Plus, they are more suitable for applications involving carcinogenic gases like BTEX and H2S applications. Incineration of waste gas products may not be a new concept for the                  oil and gas industry however, in recent years the design and technology have resulted in optimal performance, increased reliability and reduce capital and operating costs for operators.                  An enclosed combustor is a newer iteration of the incinerator. The combustion device is completely enclosed except for the combustion air intake and the exhaust discharge. It operates like an incinerator with more restriction to allow it to be able to operate in a reduced spacing capacity. The surfaces exposed to the atmosphere operate below the temperature that would ignite a flammable substance present in the surrounding area. Because of the reduced space capacity all air intakes must be equipped with a flame arresting device as a safety feature to allow the unit to be 10 meters away from wells or operating equipment. https://energynow.com/2021/07/the-differences-between-flares-incinerators-and-enclosed-combustors/</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um incinerador é um forno que é projetado para combustir material de resíduo para fins de descarte.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An incinerator is a furnace that is designed to combust waste material for disposal purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Incinerator(x) ↔ Furnace(x) ∧ ∃f(WasteCombustionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">incinerador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">incinerator</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every incinerator is a furnace that bears a waste combustion function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1970"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000115">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1263"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' and a 'gas pressure increase device' that is intended to deliver or exhaust volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FAN&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;DELIVERING&gt; or &lt;EXHAUSTING&gt; volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to deliver or exhaust volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fan is an assembly that bears a gas movement function, and every assembly that bears a gas movement function is a fan.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Fan(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(GasMovementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ventilador é um conjunto que possui uma função de movimentação de gás para fornecer ou exaurir volumes de vapor ou gás com baixa pressão diferencial.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fan is an assembly that bears a gas movement function for delivering or exhausting volumes of vapor or gas at low differential pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">ventilador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fan</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1975">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WasteFeedSystem"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000271">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameArrestor(x) ↔ SafetyDevice(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameArrestFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame arrestor is a safety device that has the function of arresting flames and processes gaseous portions while preventing flame propagation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">arrestador de chama</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame arrestor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um arrestador de chama é um dispositivo de segurança que possui uma função de arrestar chama para prevenir que chamas entrem em um sistema através de uma abertura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame arrestor is a safety device that bears a flame arrest function to prevent flames from entering a system through an opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME ARRESTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ARRESTOR&gt; that is a trap covering an opening, e.g of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An arrestor which is a trap over an opening, e.g. of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1362"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb258">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RapidDepressurizationProcess"/>
