    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowTubeOscillationDriver">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow tube oscillation driver</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">acionador de fluxo de tubo de oscilação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb9">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AbsorptionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RotaryDisplacementMechanism">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo rotativo de deslocamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotary displacement mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000140">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification requires necessary conditions only. Under OWA, any artifact with a plug closure and quarter-turn mechanism would be forcibly classified as a plug valve, but specialized multi-port valves or custom manifolds containing plug mechanisms should not automatically inherit the standard plug valve classification without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every plug valve is a valve that has a plug closure component and participates in quarter-turn rotation processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula plug</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">plug valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula plug é uma válvula que possui um elemento de fechamento em forma de plugue cilíndrico ou cônico que opera por rotação de um quarto de volta em seu eixo para controlar o fluxo de fluido selando contra um assento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A plug valve is a valve that has a cylindrical or tapered plug closure member which operates by quarter-turn rotation on its axis to control fluid flow by sealing against a seat.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PlugValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃p(PlugClosure(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃r(QuarterTurnRotationProcess(r) ∧ participatesIn(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PLUG VALVE&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY VALVE&gt; that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A high pressure valve with a rotatable plug that allows or denies flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A rotary valve that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary valve that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A quarter-turn valve whose closure element is usually a tapered plug having a rectangular port.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2487"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2486"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AirOutlet">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">air outlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">saída de ar</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000224">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que é especificamente projetado e dimensionado para compatibilidade estrutural com mecanismos de compressor centrífugo, fornecendo contenção e proteção para impulsores rotativos e componentes de fluxo associados.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that is specifically designed and dimensioned for structural compatibility with centrifugal compressor mechanisms, providing enclosure and protection for rotating impellers and associated flow components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb430"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal compressor casing</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CentrifugalCompressorCasing(x) → Casing(x) ∧ ∃y(CentrifugalCompressor(y) ∧ intendedFor(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL COMPRESSOR CASING&gt; is a &lt;COMPRESSOR CASING&gt; that is intended to be used for a centrifugal compressor.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural compatibility. Under OWA, asserting equivalence could force classification of any casing with centrifugal compressor compatibility, including hybrid or specialized equipment that should not be automatically classified as standard centrifugal compressor casings.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal compressor casing is a casing that is intended for use with centrifugal compressors</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1619">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1615"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000080">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for 'seat' based solely on structural properties could lead to false positives where other valve components with sealing surfaces are incorrectly classified as seats.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2880"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Seat(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(SealingSurface(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(ValveClosingProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that has a sealing surface component and participates in valve closing processes, consisting in that part of a valve against which the closure element bears to provide tight shutoff.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui um componente de superfície de vedação e participa em processos de fechamento de válvulas, consistindo na parte da válvula contra a qual o elemento de fechamento se apoia para proporcionar vedação hermética.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">seat</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">assento</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] That part of a valve against which the closure element (gate, ball) affects a tight shutoff.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Seat is a MaterialArtifact that has some sealing surface component at all times and participates in some valve closing process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DetectionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb890"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb889"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de detecção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">detection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000136">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2308"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2307"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000082"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(OrificePlate(x) → FlowMeasuringElement(x) ∧ ∃p,h(ThinPlate(p) ∧ SpecifiedHole(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃f(FlowMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An orifice plate is a flow measuring element that consists of a thin plate with a specified hole through which fluid flows to create differential pressure for flow rate measurement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma placa de orifício é um elemento de medição de fluxo que consiste de uma placa fina com um orifício especificado através do qual o fluido flui para criar pressão diferencial para medição da taxa de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every orifice plate is a flow measuring element that has a thin plate component and has a specified hole component and bears a flow measurement function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">placa de orifício</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">orifice plate</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, any plate with a hole could potentially be classified as an orifice plate, but many perforated plates serve different purposes (structural, filtering, etc.). The structural differentia alone is not sufficient without industrial context validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a thin plate with a specified hole in the middle. It is usually placed in a pipe to measure the rate of fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Part of an orifice metering system. A plate with a hole through which a single phase flow produces a pressure drop.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2038">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000029"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb981">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DifferentialPressureMeasurementProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000295">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Mixing chamber where dry components can be evenly mixed with liquids. The dry materials are introduced at the bottom of the hopper through a nozzle.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The device used to facilitate the addition of drilling fluid additives to the whole mud system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOPPER&gt; is a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; with a conical shape that is intended to store solids for filling or dosing purposes</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Hopper(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(SolidDischargeOpening(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hopper is a vessel that bears a SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction and has a SolidDischargeOpening as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1843"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um hopper é um vaso projetado para armazenar materiais sólidos e dispensá-los através de uma abertura de descarga controlada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hopper is a vessel that is designed to store solid materials and dispense them through a controlled discharge opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">hopper</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hopper</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlameSensingElement">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame sensing element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de chama de sensoriamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SensingElement"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/IntakeValve">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">intake valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de admissão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1048">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InformationDisplayFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb615">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb561">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InterruptingMedium"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000217">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every boiler is a heater that bears a BoilingFunction and has component parts including a steam drum and heat exchange surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb292"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma caldeira é um aquecedor que leva um líquido ao seu ponto de ebulição através de troca de calor por contato indireto, produzindo vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A boiler is a heater that brings a liquid to its boiling point through indirect contact heat exchange, producing steam or vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An indirect contact heat exchanger that is intended to heat a liquid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A that brings a liquid to its boiling point.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BOILER&gt; is a &lt;HEATER&gt; that brings a &lt;LIQUID&gt; to its boiling point</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Boiler(x) ↔ Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(BoilingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">boiler</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">caldeira</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1647">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalEnergyGenerationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
