  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000355">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Stator is a MaterialArtifact that bears a StationaryMachineComponentFunction and is part of some RotatingMachine</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3047"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3046"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma StationaryMachineComponentFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Stator(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(StationaryMachineComponentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(RotatingMachine(m) ∧ partOf(x,m)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on structural positioning within rotating machinery. Under OWA, any artifact described as stationary within a rotating machine context could be classified as a stator, but this may include specialized hybrid components, mounting structures, or custom configurations that should not be automatically asserted into the standard stator maintenance category. The structural differentia (stationary positioning) is necessary but making it sufficient requires domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;STATOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the arrangement of primary coils being the stator winding and being the stationary part of a machine</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In the context of a PDM motor, a stator is the stationary rubber element of a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a StationaryMachineComponentFunction and that is the stationary structural component within rotating machinery, providing housing and positional stability for active elements such as windings, vanes, or seals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma StationaryMachineComponentFunction e que é o componente estrutural estacionário dentro de máquinas rotativas, fornecendo alojamento e estabilidade posicional para elementos ativos como bobinas, palhetas ou vedações.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000292">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador gravitacional é um separador que realiza separação baseada nas diferenças de gravidade específica das substâncias sendo separadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gravity separator is a separator that performs separation based on differences in specific gravity of the substances being separated.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1781"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gravity separator is a separator that bears a GravitySeparationFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A separator that is based on the difference in specific gravity for the substances to be separated.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GRAVITY SEPARATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID SEPARATOR&gt; that is based on the difference in specific gravity for the substances to be separated</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A separator that is based on the difference in specific gravity for the substances to be separated.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador gravitacional</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gravity separator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GravitySeparator(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(GravitySeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1003">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1008"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb388">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb392"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000119">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1702"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1701"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gate control valve is a control valve that uses a gate or wedge closure element moving perpendicular to the flow path to modulate fluid flow in response to control signals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle tipo gaveta é uma válvula de controle que usa um elemento de fechamento tipo gaveta ou cunha movendo-se perpendicular ao caminho do fluxo para modular o fluxo de fluido em resposta a sinais de controle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A control valve that is a gate valve and an actuated valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GATE CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; and a &lt;GATE VALVE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle tipo gaveta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gate control valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gate control valve is a control valve that has a gate closure mechanism as component part at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive subtype where the structural differentia (gate closure mechanism) defines necessary conditions. Under OWA, making this sufficient could force any assembly with a gate closure into this maintenance category, including specialized multi-way valves or custom manifolds that should not be classified as standard gate control valves.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GateControlValve(x) → ControlValve(x) ∧ ∃g(GateClosureMechanism(g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MultiphaseFluidPortion">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">multiphase fluid portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção multifásico de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FormationFluidPortion">
