    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">dehydration function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb743">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ConnectionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1460">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VaporOutlet"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000107">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COALESCER&gt; is a &lt;GRAVITY SEPARATOR&gt; where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every coalescer is a separator that bears a coalescence function and participates in gravity separation processes to produce skimmable liquid portions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coalescedor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coalescer</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb576"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A coalescer is a separator that uses coalescence media to promote droplet merger in immiscible liquid mixtures, enabling gravity-based separation where the less dense liquid phase can be skimmed off.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um coalescedor é um separador que usa meio de coalescência para promover a fusão de gotículas em misturas líquidas imiscíveis, permitindo separação por gravidade onde a fase líquida menos densa pode ser removida por escumação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Coalescer(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(CoalescenceFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(GravitySeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃o(SkimmableLiquidPortion(o) ∧ hasOutput(x,o))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TubingString">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de coluna de produção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing string</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1286">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1287"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1282"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000160">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A wafer pattern valve that is a check valve with a wafer pattern valve body.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WAFER CHECK VALVE&gt; is a &lt;WAFER PATTERN VALVE&gt; and a &lt;CHECK VALVE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A wafer pattern valve that is a check valve with a wafer pattern valve body.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wafer check valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de retenção wafer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3443"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3442"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A wafer check valve is a check valve that has a wafer pattern valve body designed for mounting between flanges.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de retenção wafer é uma válvula de retenção que possui um corpo de válvula padrão wafer projetado para montagem entre flanges.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every wafer check valve is a check valve that has a wafer pattern valve body as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(WaferCheckValve(x) → CheckValve(x) ∧ ∃y(WaferPatternValveBody(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive subtype (both functional and structural aspects). The wafer pattern mounting configuration is a structural differentia that, while characteristic, may have edge cases or specialized variants that should not be automatically classified without expert validation. The structural differentia should be confirmed as both necessary and sufficient in industrial practice before upgrading to equivalent mode.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ShapedOrifice">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">orifício de perfilado</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaped orifice</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
