  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HeatTransferProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat transfer process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de transferência de calor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which thermal energy is transferred between two or more fluid streams through a solid boundary, enabling temperature equalization or thermal conditioning without direct mixing of the media.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2989">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SolidBulkStorageFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000227">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ClosureMember"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb476"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000370"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é uma parte componente de uma válvula de retenção e que possui uma BackflowPreventionFunction, consistindo em um elemento mecânico que previne o refluxo de fluido bloqueando fisicamente o caminho de fluxo quando as condições de pressão indicam potencial refluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is a component part of a check valve and that bears a BackflowPreventionFunction, consisting in a mechanical element that prevents fluid flow reversal by physically blocking the flow path when pressure conditions indicate potential backflow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve closure member</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">membro de fechamento de válvula de retenção</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValveClosureMember(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(CheckValve(y) ∧ isComponentPartOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(BackflowPreventionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; that is intended to prevent back flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every check valve closure member is a MaterialArtifact that is component part of some check valve and bears some BackflowPreventionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural role and mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force classification of any artifact with backflow prevention function and check valve association, potentially including hybrid or specialized designs that should not be automatically classified as standard closure members without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb430">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CoolingProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de resfriamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cooling process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000134">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A needle valve is a valve that has a conical needle-shaped closure member that seats into a small orifice to provide precise flow control.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula agulha é uma válvula que possui um membro de fechamento cônico em forma de agulha que se assenta em um pequeno orifício para fornecer controle preciso de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">needle valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula agulha</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every needle valve is a valve that has a needle plug component and has a small orifice seat component.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of small valve used for flow metering, having a tapered needlepoint plug or closure element and a seat having a small orifice.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;NEEDLE VALVE&gt; is a &lt;GLOBE VALVE&gt; that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A low volume, small orifice, high pressure bleed valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A globe valve that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A globe valve that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2278"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(NeedleValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y(NeedlePlug(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(SmallOrificeSeat(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by specific structural features (needle plug geometry), providing sufficient conditions under the Open World Assumption could lead to over-classification. Complex valve assemblies or custom equipment containing needle-like mechanisms might be incorrectly classified as standard needle valves for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RotatingShaft">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotating shaft</rdfs:label>
