  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000313">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A mill is usually used to remove junk in the hole or to grind away all or part of a casing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cutting tool used to grind up metal, dress off a fish, or open up a window for a kick-off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MILL&gt; is a &lt;FACILITY&gt; that consists of the land, buildings, machinery, apparatus, and fixtures, mostly employed in &lt;MANUFACTURING&gt; of discrete &lt;COMMODITY MATERIAL&gt;s</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um moinho é um conjunto que possui uma função de processamento de material para reduzir o tamanho de partículas ou modificar materiais sólidos através de operações mecânicas de moagem, corte ou trituração.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A mill is an assembly that bears a material processing function to reduce particle size or modify solid materials through mechanical grinding, cutting, or crushing operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every mill is an assembly that has the function to process materials, and every assembly that has the function to process materials is a mill.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Mill(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(MaterialProcessingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2221"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mill</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">moinho</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000170">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de segurança subsuperficial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">subsurface safety function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1090"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000032"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1091"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ShaftSeal">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vedação de eixo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft seal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000212">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb120"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from the medium of lower conductivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The positively charged site in a cell. Oxidation site. The site of metal loss in corrosion.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The half of a battery that is positively charged and to which anions migrate by electrostatic attraction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ANODE&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL DEVICE&gt; that has a capability of &lt;EMITTING&gt; positive charge carriers to, and/or &lt;RECEIVING&gt; negative charge carriers from, the medium of lower conductivity</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An anode is electrical equipment that bears the function of serving as the positive electrode in electrochemical processes, capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from a medium of lower conductivity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ânodo é um equipamento elétrico que possui a função de servir como eletrodo positivo em processos eletroquímicos, capaz de emitir portadores de carga positiva para e/ou receber portadores de carga negativa de um meio de menor condutividade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Anode(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(AnodeFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every anode is electrical equipment that has the function of electrochemical oxidation and has electrical connection and active material as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">ânodo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">anode</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
