  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000154">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (TemperatureIndicator(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (TemperatureIndicationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s (TemperatureSensingElement(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃d (LocalDisplay(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature indicator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">indicador de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um indicador de temperatura é um indicador que mede temperatura e exibe o valor medido localmente na localização do instrumento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A temperature indicator is an indicator that measures temperature and displays the measured value locally at the instrument location.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] A temperature indicator (TI) is an instrument that measures temperature and displays the measured value locally at the instrument location. It typically consists of a temperature sensing element (thermocouple, RTD, or bimetal), a transmitting or mechanical linkage, and a local display. Unlike a temperature transmitter, it does not produce a standardized remote output signal; its function is limited to local indication for operator reading.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every temperature indicator is an instrument that has the function of temperature indication and has component parts including a temperature sensing element and a local display.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3129"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionPort">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection port</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bocal de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000135">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An on-off control valve is a control valve that bears a binary flow control function, having only two defined positions: fully open and fully closed.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle liga-desliga é uma válvula de controle que possui uma função de controle de fluxo binária, tendo apenas duas posições definidas: totalmente aberta e totalmente fechada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle liga-desliga</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">on off control valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(OnOffControlValve(x) ↔ ControlValve(x) ∧ ∃f(BinaryFlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ON-OFF CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; that only has two defined positions, being fully open and fully closed</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2299"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every on-off control valve is a control valve that has a BinaryFlowControlFunction and has component part a BinaryPositioner.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
