  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PowerTransmissionProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de transmissão de potência</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">power transmission process</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transferred from a prime mover through a rotating shaft to one or more driven machines, typically involving the conversion of torque and rotational speed to match operational requirements.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transmitted from a driving component to a driven component through the rotation or linear motion of a shaft, enabling the transfer of torque and rotational speed.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transmitted through rotational motion from one component to another via a rotating shaft, enabling the transfer of torque and angular velocity to mounted components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which mechanical power is transferred from one rotating or reciprocating component to another through direct mechanical engagement, resulting in motion transmission and potentially torque or speed modification.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transmitted from an external energy source through a rotating shaft to downstream mechanical components, enabling power transfer within a mechanical system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which mechanical rotational energy is transmitted from a prime mover through a shaft to driven components, resulting in the transfer of torque and rotational motion necessary for equipment operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000213">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de deslocamento axial é um transmissor que mede deslocamento axial e gera um sinal de saída padronizado representando o deslocamento axial medido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An axial displacement transmitter is a transmitter that measures axial displacement and generates a standardized output signal representing the measured axial displacement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;AXIAL DISPLACEMENT TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;DISPLACEMENT TRANSMITTER&gt; for &lt;AXIAL DISPLACEMENT&gt; measurement, using an &lt;AXIAL DISPLACEMENT MEASURING PROBE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transmitter measuring an axial displacement and generating a standardized output signal representing the axial measured displacement.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb132"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(AxialDisplacementTransmitter(x) ↔ (Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(AxialDisplacementTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(AxialDisplacementMeasuringProbe(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de deslocamento axial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">axial displacement transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every axial displacement transmitter is a transmitter that has the function to measure axial displacement and has as component part an axial displacement measuring probe.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000348">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shear ram</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aríete de corte</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shear ram is a ram that bears a pipe shearing function and has hardened cutting blades designed to cut drillpipe or tubing during blowout prevention operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aríete de corte é um aríete que possui função de corte de tubulação e tem lâminas de corte endurecidas projetadas para cortar a coluna de perfuração ou tubulação durante operações de prevenção de blowout.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shear ram is a ram that has the function to shear pipe and has shearing blades as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAR RAM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;RAM&gt; that is a closure mechanism on a wells blowout-preventer stack fitted with chisel-like jaws that are hydraulically operated. When the ram is closed on the pipe, the jaws or blades cut the pipe, permitting the upper section to be removed from the BOP stack</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A ram in the BOP that shears off the pipe.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A shear valve is a ram-type BOP, similar in operation to a gate valve, but uses a pair of opposing steel plungers, rams. The rams extend toward the centre of the wellbore to restrict flow or retract open in order to permit flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A blowout preventer (BOP) closing element fitted with hardened tool steel blades designed to cut the drillpipe or tubing when the BOP is closed, and then fully close to provide isolation or sealing of the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2934"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ShearRam(x) ↔ Ram(x) ∧ ∃f(PipeShearingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃b(ShearingBlade(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
