  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000130">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2114"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um visor de nível é um visor que possui uma função projetada para indicar o nível de líquido através de inspeção visual.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A level sight glass is a sight glass that bears a designed function to indicate liquid level through visual inspection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level sight glass</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">visor de nível</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (LevelSightGlass(x) ↔ SightGlass(x) ∧ ∃f (LevelIndicationFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;LEVEL SIGHT GLASS&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;SIGHT GLASS&gt; mounted in or on a pipe or vessel to see inside for liquid level inspection</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every level sight glass is a sight glass that has the function of level indication.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000291">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb1776"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula globo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">globe valve body</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GLOBE VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; of a globe valve</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GlobeValveBody(x) → ValveBody(x) ∧ ∃g (GlobularGeometry(g) ∧ hasDesignCharacteristic(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A valve body that has a globular geometry designed to accommodate the perpendicular flow path and disc closure mechanism characteristic of globe valve operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um corpo de válvula que possui geometria globular projetada para acomodar o caminho de fluxo perpendicular e o mecanismo de fechamento por disco característico da operação de válvula globo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every globe valve body is a valve body that has globular geometry for perpendicular flow path accommodation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural geometry. Under OWA, asserting equivalence based on globular geometry alone could lead to false classifications of complex assemblies or hybrid components that contain globular elements but should not be classified as standard globe valve bodies.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000304">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every injection pump is a pump that bears an injection function for delivering fluids to reservoirs or production systems.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection pump</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb2008"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Any pump used to inject fluid into the reservoir or production system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INJECTION PUMP&gt; is a &lt; POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; that is typically applied for relatively high pressures in case of injection systems</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An injection pump is a pump that is specifically designed to inject fluid into reservoirs or production systems, typically at relatively high pressures.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de injeção é uma bomba especificamente projetada para injetar fluido em reservatórios ou sistemas de produção, tipicamente em pressões relativamente altas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(InjectionPump(x) ↔ Pump(x) ∧ ∃f(InjectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
  </rdf:Description>
