  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000366">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina é um conjunto que possui uma função de extração de energia e tem eixo rotativo e pás de interação com fluidos que extraem energia de fluidos em movimento e a convertem em trabalho mecânico útil.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has rotating shaft and fluid-interacting blades that extract energy from flowing fluids and convert it into useful mechanical work.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to rotate within a fluid and to transform energy within a fluid into mechanical power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An object that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TURBINE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DRIVER(function)&gt; that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbine</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has component parts including a rotating shaft, fluid interaction blades, casing, and bearing system.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb3289"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Turbine(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnergyExtractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(RotatingShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃b(FluidInteractionBlades(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb31">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb27"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DrillingFluid">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fluido de perfuração</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drilling fluid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula choke</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">choke valve</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function and has a flow restriction element as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function, designed to reduce fluid pressure from inlet to outlet through controlled flow restriction and energy dissipation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula choke é uma válvula que possui uma função de redução de pressão, projetada para reduzir a pressão do fluido da entrada para a saída através de restrição controlada do fluxo e dissipação de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHOKE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; in which a solid cylinder is raised and lowered, and which is placed around or inside another cylinder that has holes or slots. The design of a choke valve means fluids flowing through the cage are coming from all sides and that the streams of flow (through the holes or slots) collide with each other at the center of the cage cylinder, thereby dissipating the energy of the fluid through flow impingement. The main advantage of choke valves is that they can be designed to be totally linear in their flow rate</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n77c2a26f99c94a33993b8edf520dd96cb496"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChokeValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
